## Next Steps

1. **DTLS Chunk WGLC:** **Magnus Westerlund** and the author team will resolve one minor editorial item regarding the abstract vs. socket API text, after which the chairs intend to issue a Working Group Last Call for `draft-ietf-tsvwg-sctp-dtls-chunk` before the San Francisco meeting.
2. **Key Management Adopt/Design Call:** The working group will discuss the new TLS 1.3 key management proposal on the mailing list. An adoption call is planned around or shortly after the San Francisco meeting.
3. **FQ-PIE WGLC:** The chairs will initiate a Working Group Last Call for `draft-ietf-tsvwg-fq-pie` in the near future, potentially prior to the San Francisco meeting.
4. **L4Sops Path Forward:** Due to split feedback on whether to ship the current document or wait for the SRM draft, the chairs will take this discussion to the mailing list to establish consensus.
5. **SCTP Negotiation Acceleration Protocol:** Technical discussions on SDP parameter formatting and architectural viability will continue on the TSVWG list to determine which WG should adopt the work.